\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa360\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Scrivener\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s editor has four possible modes\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 four different ways of viewing your work. Learning how and when to switch between them will make your Scrivener experience much more productive. You switch between these modes using the }{\f1\fs22\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>View Mode<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  control in the toolbar, which looks like this:}
